fields.specialist_description: A neurologist is a medical doctor who diagnoses, treats and manages disorders of the brain and nervous system (brain, spinal cord and nerves). A neurologist knows the anatomy, function and conditions that affect your nerves and nervous system.
All types of heart surgery including heart transplant, surgery, ring fitting, pressmaker placement.
All types of heart surgery including heart transplant, surgery, ring fitting, pressmaker placement.

Orthopedics or orthopedic surgery is a type of surgical medical branch that deals with bones and muscles as well as the skeletal system. Orthopedic surgeons perform this treatment with or without surgery.
All types of heart surgery including heart transplant, surgery, ring fitting, pressmaker placement.
All types of heart surgery including heart transplant, surgery, ring fitting, pressmaker placement.

Gastroenterologists are medical doctors who specialize in diagnosing and treating disorders of the digestive system, including the esophagus, stomach, intestines, liver, gallbladder, and pancreas. They diagnose conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), and liver cirrhosis, and provide treatments such as endoscopy, colonoscopy, and medication management.

A psychologist is a trained mental health professional who helps people learn healthy ways to handle mental health challenges. They can help people living with specific conditions, like depression or anxiety, or those who are going through a tough time in life, like grieving the loss of a loved one.

A dermatologist is responsible for the detection and treatment of skin- and sexually transmitted diseases. The dermatologist is dedicated to delivering preventive care, follow-up care and rehabilitation with regard to diseases afflicting the skin, mucous membranes and skin appendages  such as nails and hair.

A gynecologist is a doctor who specializes in female reproductive health. They diagnose and treat issues related to the female reproductive tract. This includes the uterus, fallopian tubes, ovaries, and breasts.

A surgeon is someone who specializes in treating patients with surgery or operations. A surgeon can be a general surgeon i.e. operating on different parts of the body or a specialized surgeon i.e. cardiac surgeon neurosurgeon etc.

Urology specialists treat various diseases of the human urinary system. In simple words, urology specialist doctor provides necessary treatment including surgery for various urinary problems, urinary bladder or kidney stone problems and various problems of these organs.
